John Renbourn is an English guitarist and songwriter. He is possibly best known for his collaboration with guitarists Stfean Grossman and Bert Jansch as well as his work with the folk group Pentangle, although he maintained a solo career both before, during and after that band's existence (1967-1973).

While most commonly labelled a folk musician, Renbourn's musical tastes and interests take in early music, classical music, blues and world music.
